{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":681,"text":"I'm here today to talk about a disturbing question,"},{"time":3969,"text":"which has an equally disturbing answer."},{"time":7667,"text":"My topic is the secrets of domestic violence,"},{"time":11269,"text":"and the question I'm going to tackle"},{"time":13603,"text":"is the one question everyone always asks:"},{"time":17684,"text":"Why does she stay?"},{"time":19296,"text":"Why would anyone stay with a man who beats her?"},{"time":23292,"text":"I'm not a psychiatrist, a social worker"},{"time":26269,"text":"or an expert in domestic violence."},{"time":28604,"text":"I'm just one woman with a story to tell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31803,"text":"I was 22. I had just graduated from Harvard College."},{"time":36316,"text":"I had moved to New York City for my first job"},{"time":38788,"text":"as a writer and editor at Seventeen magazine."},{"time":42084,"text":"I had my first apartment,"},{"time":44324,"text":"my first little green American Express card,"},{"time":47524,"text":"and I had a very big secret."},{"time":50552,"text":"My secret was that I had this gun"},{"time":54251,"text":"loaded with hollow-point bullets pointed at my head"},{"time":57689,"text":"by the man who I thought was my soulmate,"},{"time":60252,"text":"many, many times."},{"time":63737,"text":"The man who I loved more than anybody on Earth"},{"time":67297,"text":"held a gun to my head and threatened to kill me"},{"time":71376,"text":"more times than I can even remember."},{"time":74561,"text":"I'm here to tell you the story of crazy love,"},{"time":77304,"text":"a psychological trap disguised as love,"},{"time":80488,"text":"one that millions of women and even a few men"},{"time":83340,"text":"fall into every year."},{"time":85721,"text":"It may even be your story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88470,"text":"I don't look like a typical domestic violence survivor."},{"time":91513,"text":"I have a B.A. in English from Harvard College,"},{"time":93819,"text":"an MBA in marketing from Wharton Business School."},{"time":96181,"text":"I've spent most of my career working for Fortune 500 companies"},{"time":99473,"text":"including Johnson &amp; Johnson, Leo Burnett and The Washington Post."},{"time":103745,"text":"I've been married for almost 20 years to my second husband"},{"time":107541,"text":"and we have three kids together."},{"time":110330,"text":"My dog is a black lab, and I drive a Honda Odyssey minivan."},{"time":114559,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117039,"text":"So my first message for you is that domestic violence"},{"time":119758,"text":"happens to everyone --"},{"time":122126,"text":"all races, all religions, all income and education levels."},{"time":126302,"text":"It's everywhere."},{"time":128241,"text":"And my second message is that everyone thinks"},{"time":130761,"text":"domestic violence happens to women,"},{"time":132879,"text":"that it's a women's issue."},{"time":135147,"text":"Not exactly."},{"time":137366,"text":"Over 85 percent of abusers are men, and domestic abuse"},{"time":141478,"text":"happens only in intimate, interdependent, long-term relationships,"},{"time":147396,"text":"in other words, in families,"},{"time":149565,"text":"the last place we would want or expect to find violence,"},{"time":153430,"text":"which is one reason domestic abuse is so confusing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157708,"text":"I would have told you myself that I was the last person on Earth"},{"time":161259,"text":"who would stay with a man who beats me,"},{"time":163831,"text":"but in fact I was a very typical victim because of my age."},{"time":167238,"text":"I was 22, and in the United States,"},{"time":170523,"text":"women ages 16 to 24 are three times as likely"},{"time":174372,"text":"to be domestic violence victims"},{"time":177133,"text":"as women of other ages,"},{"time":179948,"text":"and over 500 women and girls this age"},{"time":183251,"text":"are killed every year by abusive partners,"},{"time":186822,"text":"boyfriends, and husbands in the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191455,"text":"I was also a very typical victim because I knew nothing"},{"time":194515,"text":"about domestic violence, its warning signs or its patterns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199100,"text":"I met Conor on a cold, rainy January night."},{"time":204165,"text":"He sat next to me on the New York City subway,"},{"time":207128,"text":"and he started chatting me up."},{"time":209267,"text":"He told me two things."},{"time":211135,"text":"One was that he, too, had just graduated from an Ivy League school,"},{"time":214937,"text":"and that he worked at a very impressive Wall Street bank."},{"time":219292,"text":"But what made the biggest impression on me that first meeting"},{"time":222952,"text":"was that he was smart and funny"},{"time":226240,"text":"and he looked like a farm boy."},{"time":227640,"text":"He had these big cheeks, these big apple cheeks"},{"time":229987,"text":"and this wheat-blond hair,"},{"time":231672,"text":"and he seemed so sweet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234959,"text":"One of the smartest things Conor did, from the very beginning,"},{"time":238743,"text":"was to create the illusion that I was the dominant partner in the relationship."},{"time":244317,"text":"He did this especially at the beginning"},{"time":246518,"text":"by idolizing me."},{"time":249384,"text":"We started dating, and he loved everything about me,"},{"time":252670,"text":"that I was smart, that I'd gone to Harvard,"},{"time":254354,"text":"that I was passionate about helping teenage girls, and my job."},{"time":257384,"text":"He wanted to know everything about my family"},{"time":259915,"text":"and my childhood and my hopes and dreams."},{"time":262531,"text":"Conor believed in me, as a writer and a woman,"},{"time":266165,"text":"in a way that no one else ever had."},{"time":269844,"text":"And he also created a magical atmosphere of trust between us"},{"time":274169,"text":"by confessing his secret,"},{"time":276689,"text":"which was that, as a very young boy starting at age four,"},{"time":281169,"text":"he had been savagely and repeatedly physically abused"},{"time":284080,"text":"by his stepfather,"},{"time":285766,"text":"and the abuse had gotten so bad that he had had to drop out of school in eighth grade,"},{"time":289706,"text":"even though he was very smart,"},{"time":292325,"text":"and he'd spent almost 20 years rebuilding his life."},{"time":295581,"text":"Which is why that Ivy League degree"},{"time":298737,"text":"and the Wall Street job and his bright shiny future"},{"time":301550,"text":"meant so much to him."},{"time":304121,"text":"If you had told me"},{"time":306265,"text":"that this smart, funny, sensitive man who adored me"},{"time":311629,"text":"would one day dictate whether or not I wore makeup,"},{"time":316012,"text":"how short my skirts were,"},{"time":318062,"text":"where I lived, what jobs I took,"},{"time":319992,"text":"who my friends were and where I spent Christmas,"},{"time":323356,"text":"I would have laughed at you,"},{"time":325304,"text":"because there was not a hint of violence or control"},{"time":328352,"text":"or anger in Conor at the beginning."},{"time":331836,"text":"I didn't know that the first stage"},{"time":334961,"text":"in any domestic violence relationship"},{"time":337336,"text":"is to seduce and charm the victim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340988,"text":"I also didn't know that the second step is to isolate the victim."},{"time":345748,"text":"Now, Conor did not come home one day and announce,"},{"time":349902,"text":"\"You know, hey, all this Romeo and Juliet stuff has been great,"},{"time":353036,"text":"but I need to move into the next phase"},{"time":355041,"text":"where I isolate you and I abuse you\" — (Laughter) —"},{"time":359220,"text":"\"so I need to get you out of this apartment"},{"time":360575,"text":"where the neighbors can hear you scream"},{"time":362216,"text":"and out of this city where you have friends and family"},{"time":364689,"text":"and coworkers who can see the bruises.\""},{"time":367995,"text":"Instead, Conor came home one Friday evening"},{"time":372216,"text":"and he told me that he had quit his job that day,"},{"time":374947,"text":"his dream job,"},{"time":377412,"text":"and he said that he had quit his job because of me,"},{"time":381553,"text":"because I had made him feel so safe and loved"},{"time":384731,"text":"that he didn't need to prove himself on Wall Street anymore,"},{"time":387854,"text":"and he just wanted to get out of the city"},{"time":390369,"text":"and away from his abusive, dysfunctional family,"},{"time":393347,"text":"and move to a tiny town in New England"},{"time":396469,"text":"where he could start his life over with me by his side."},{"time":400042,"text":"Now, the last thing I wanted to do was leave New York,"},{"time":403908,"text":"and my dream job,"},{"time":407515,"text":"but I thought you made sacrifices for your soulmate,"},{"time":410098,"text":"so I agreed, and I quit my job,"},{"time":413562,"text":"and Conor and I left Manhattan together."},{"time":416193,"text":"I had no idea I was falling into crazy love,"},{"time":420559,"text":"that I was walking headfirst into a carefully laid"},{"time":424191,"text":"physical, financial and psychological trap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429171,"text":"The next step in the domestic violence pattern"},{"time":431491,"text":"is to introduce the threat of violence"},{"time":435773,"text":"and see how she reacts."},{"time":437972,"text":"And here's where those guns come in."},{"time":440681,"text":"As soon as we moved to New England -- you know,"},{"time":443599,"text":"that place where Connor was supposed to feel so safe --"},{"time":446337,"text":"he bought three guns."},{"time":448753,"text":"He kept one in the glove compartment of our car."},{"time":452193,"text":"He kept one under the pillows on our bed,"},{"time":454849,"text":"and the third one he kept in his pocket at all times."},{"time":458011,"text":"And he said that he needed those guns"},{"time":460329,"text":"because of the trauma he'd experienced as a young boy."},{"time":463125,"text":"He needed them to feel protected."},{"time":465609,"text":"But those guns were really a message for me,"},{"time":468521,"text":"and even though he hadn't raised a hand to me,"},{"time":471215,"text":"my life was already in grave danger every minute of every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477021,"text":"Conor first physically attacked me"},{"time":480594,"text":"five days before our wedding."},{"time":483419,"text":"It was 7 a.m. I still had on my nightgown."},{"time":487611,"text":"I was working on my computer trying to finish a freelance writing assignment,"},{"time":491851,"text":"and I got frustrated,"},{"time":493665,"text":"and Conor used my anger as an excuse"},{"time":496752,"text":"to put both of his hands around my neck"},{"time":499903,"text":"and to squeeze so tightly that I could not breathe or scream,"},{"time":503723,"text":"and he used the chokehold"},{"time":505547,"text":"to hit my head repeatedly against the wall."},{"time":509973,"text":"Five days later, the ten bruises on my neck had just faded,"},{"time":515291,"text":"and I put on my mother's wedding dress,"},{"time":517766,"text":"and I married him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520083,"text":"Despite what had happened,"},{"time":522364,"text":"I was sure we were going to live happily ever after,"},{"time":525883,"text":"because I loved him, and he loved me so much."},{"time":529964,"text":"And he was very, very sorry."},{"time":533336,"text":"He had just been really stressed out by the wedding"},{"time":536509,"text":"and by becoming a family with me."},{"time":538706,"text":"It was an isolated incident,"},{"time":540427,"text":"and he was never going to hurt me again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544023,"text":"It happened twice more on the honeymoon."},{"time":546603,"text":"The first time, I was driving to find a secret beach"},{"time":549690,"text":"and I got lost,"},{"time":552392,"text":"and he punched me in the side of my head so hard"},{"time":555362,"text":"that the other side of my head repeatedly hit"},{"time":557506,"text":"the driver's side window."},{"time":559913,"text":"And then a few days later, driving home from our honeymoon,"},{"time":563279,"text":"he got frustrated by traffic,"},{"time":565562,"text":"and he threw a cold Big Mac in my face."},{"time":568994,"text":"Conor proceeded to beat me once or twice a week"},{"time":571602,"text":"for the next two and a half years of our marriage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575019,"text":"I was mistaken in thinking that I was unique"},{"time":578144,"text":"and alone in this situation."},{"time":580787,"text":"One in three American women"},{"time":582978,"text":"experiences domestic violence or stalking at some point in her life,"},{"time":587130,"text":"and the CDC reports that 15 million children"},{"time":590771,"text":"are abused every year, 15 million."},{"time":594181,"text":"So actually, I was in very good company."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598554,"text":"Back to my question:"},{"time":600970,"text":"Why did I stay?"},{"time":603465,"text":"The answer is easy."},{"time":606203,"text":"I didn't know he was abusing me."},{"time":608891,"text":"Even though he held those loaded guns to my head,"},{"time":612739,"text":"pushed me down stairs,"},{"time":614962,"text":"threatened to kill our dog,"},{"time":616343,"text":"pulled the key out of the car ignition as I drove down the highway,"},{"time":620266,"text":"poured coffee grinds on my head"},{"time":622783,"text":"as I dressed for a job interview,"},{"time":625099,"text":"I never once thought of myself as a battered wife."},{"time":629469,"text":"Instead, I was a very strong woman"},{"time":633046,"text":"in love with a deeply troubled man,"},{"time":635298,"text":"and I was the only person on Earth"},{"time":637355,"text":"who could help Conor face his demons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640795,"text":"The other question everybody asks is,"},{"time":644506,"text":"why doesn't she just leave?"},{"time":646923,"text":"Why didn't I walk out? I could have left any time."},{"time":650874,"text":"To me, this is the saddest and most painful question that people ask,"},{"time":655586,"text":"because we victims know something you usually don't:"},{"time":658677,"text":"It's incredibly dangerous to leave an abuser."},{"time":663070,"text":"Because the final step in the domestic violence pattern"},{"time":666389,"text":"is kill her."},{"time":669284,"text":"Over 70 percent of domestic violence murders"},{"time":671825,"text":"happen after the victim has ended the relationship,"},{"time":675893,"text":"after she's gotten out,"},{"time":677786,"text":"because then the abuser has nothing left to lose."},{"time":681037,"text":"Other outcomes include long-term stalking,"},{"time":684128,"text":"even after the abuser remarries;"},{"time":687080,"text":"denial of financial resources;"},{"time":689235,"text":"and manipulation of the family court system"},{"time":691624,"text":"to terrify the victim and her children,"},{"time":694447,"text":"who are regularly forced by family court judges"},{"time":699373,"text":"to spend unsupervised time"},{"time":701342,"text":"with the man who beat their mother."},{"time":705013,"text":"And still we ask, why doesn't she just leave?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":709188,"text":"I was able to leave,"},{"time":710942,"text":"because of one final, sadistic beating"},{"time":713844,"text":"that broke through my denial."},{"time":717003,"text":"I realized that the man who I loved so much"},{"time":720173,"text":"was going to kill me if I let him."},{"time":723083,"text":"So I broke the silence."},{"time":725598,"text":"I told everyone:"},{"time":728428,"text":"the police, my neighbors,"},{"time":732213,"text":"my friends and family, total strangers,"},{"time":736053,"text":"and I'm here today because you all helped me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742907,"text":"We tend to stereotype victims"},{"time":745445,"text":"as grisly headlines,"},{"time":748507,"text":"self-destructive women, damaged goods."},{"time":751803,"text":"The question, \"Why does she stay?\""},{"time":754806,"text":"is code for some people for, \"It's her fault for staying,\""},{"time":760442,"text":"as if victims intentionally choose to fall in love with men"},{"time":763766,"text":"intent upon destroying us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766398,"text":"But since publishing \"Crazy Love,\""},{"time":768902,"text":"I have heard hundreds of stories from men and women"},{"time":772425,"text":"who also got out,"},{"time":774870,"text":"who learned an invaluable life lesson from what happened,"},{"time":779250,"text":"and who rebuilt lives -- joyous, happy lives --"},{"time":783463,"text":"as employees, wives and mothers,"},{"time":785797,"text":"lives completely free of violence, like me."},{"time":790478,"text":"Because it turns out that I'm actually a very typical domestic violence victim"},{"time":794509,"text":"and a typical domestic violence survivor."},{"time":797953,"text":"I remarried a kind and gentle man,"},{"time":801978,"text":"and we have those three kids."},{"time":804314,"text":"I have that black lab, and I have that minivan."},{"time":807715,"text":"What I will never have again,"},{"time":811181,"text":"ever,"},{"time":814139,"text":"is a loaded gun held to my head"},{"time":816264,"text":"by someone who says that he loves me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819907,"text":"Right now, maybe you're thinking,"},{"time":822538,"text":"\"Wow, this is fascinating,\""},{"time":824445,"text":"or, \"Wow, how stupid was she,\""},{"time":827573,"text":"but this whole time, I've actually been talking about you."},{"time":833576,"text":"I promise you there are several people"},{"time":837093,"text":"listening to me right now"},{"time":838835,"text":"who are currently being abused"},{"time":841847,"text":"or who were abused as children"},{"time":844362,"text":"or who are abusers themselves."},{"time":847732,"text":"Abuse could be affecting your daughter,"},{"time":849669,"text":"your sister, your best friend right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854962,"text":"I was able to end my own crazy love story"},{"time":858406,"text":"by breaking the silence."},{"time":860607,"text":"I'm still breaking the silence today."},{"time":863122,"text":"It's my way of helping other victims,"},{"time":866938,"text":"and it's my final request of you."},{"time":870306,"text":"Talk about what you heard here."},{"time":873138,"text":"Abuse thrives only in silence."},{"time":876466,"text":"You have the power to end domestic violence"},{"time":880169,"text":"simply by shining a spotlight on it."},{"time":883678,"text":"We victims need everyone."},{"time":886752,"text":"We need every one of you to understand"},{"time":890825,"text":"the secrets of domestic violence."},{"time":894603,"text":"Show abuse the light of day by talking about it"},{"time":897587,"text":"with your children, your coworkers,"},{"time":899714,"text":"your friends and family."},{"time":901651,"text":"Recast survivors as wonderful, lovable people"},{"time":905097,"text":"with full futures."},{"time":907912,"text":"Recognize the early signs of violence"},{"time":911393,"text":"and conscientiously intervene,"},{"time":914226,"text":"deescalate it, show victims a safe way out."},{"time":918388,"text":"Together we can make our beds,"},{"time":922383,"text":"our dinner tables and our families"},{"time":926000,"text":"the safe and peaceful oases they should be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929257,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931229,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}